  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="container my-5">
    <section id="mission">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>The Nordic Thoracic Oncology Group (NTOG) serves as a collaborative platform between the national thoracic oncology groups. We act as a common specialist medical forum for thoracic cancer to further develop lung cancer care in the Nordic countries. NTOG is a natural starting point for Nordic clinical and translational research collaboration within the field.</p>
      <p>We are professionally involved in ensuring excellent patient care, supporting patient associations, and striving for high-quality education and training for health personnel involved in the investigation and treatment of lung cancer.</p>
      
      <h3>Collaboration with National Organizations</h3>
      <p>Our mandate comes from the national thoracic oncology groups of the Nordic countries. We encourage you to visit their websites to learn more about their work:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.lungecancer.dk/" target="_blank">Danish Lung Cancer Group (Denmark)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.filha.fi/valtakunnallinen-keuhkosyopaohjelma/">Finnish Lung Cancer Group (Finland)" target="_blank"</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.krabb.is/english" target="_blank">Icelandic Oncology Society (Iceland)</a></li>
        <li><a href="http://nlcg.no" target="_blank">Norwegian Lung Cancer Group (Norway)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://slusg.org" target="_blank">Swedish Lung Cancer Study Group (Sweden)</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>By collaborating closely with these national organizations, we aim to unify efforts across borders and enhance the impact of lung cancer research and care in the Nordic region.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

